netopeer_sysrepo
----------------

To run this example NETCONF server and allow
it to manage ietf-interfaces datastore, follow
these steps, in order:


Compilation
~~~~~~~~~~~

1. north_client

$ ./configure --with-sysrepod=<path-to-sysrepod-repository> --enable-ifc-ds --disable-sshd-config-ds
$ make
# make install

2. south_client

$ make


Running
~~~~~~~

You need 3 separate terminals:

1. sysrepod

(start sysrepod with default options - no argument needed)

2. south_client

$ ./sysrepod_ifc_daemon

3. noth_client

# netopeer-sysrepo


Now you can connect to netopeer-sysrepo, it
acts as a standard NETCONF server.


sshd config
-----------

To manage sshd_config sysrepod datastore, you only
need not to disable its support during compilation.
Naturally, sysrepod must be set up correctly and
create that datastore (part of the example "param"
file in sysrepod repository).
